org.mindswap.owls.grounding
Interface JavaAtomicGrounding

All Superinterfaces:
AtomicGrounding<java.lang.Object>, OWLEntity, OWLIndividual, OWLObject, OWLValue
All Known Implementing Classes:
JavaAtomicGroundingImpl
public interface JavaAtomicGrounding
extends AtomicGrounding<java.lang.Object>

This interface encapsulates the access to a JavaAtomicProcessGrounding.

A JavaAtomicGrounding grounds an OWL-S Service to a Java method invocation. The method call is specified by its method signature in an OWL-S Ontology.

Static methods can be invoked, exceptions during the execution are catched and redirected in a ExecutionException. At the time, only primitive datatypes (such as int, boolean, and so on) and their wrappers (such as Integer, Boolean, and so on) are supported.

The driving parts are:

  • fully qualified class name
  • method name
  • a map of all input parameters (at the time only primitive datatypes and their wrapper classes)
  • an output type (at the time only primitive datatypes and their wrapper classes)

See Also:
MoreGroundings.owl, MoreGroundings
